I've been shot at by younger.

114
00:06:05,164 --> 00:06:05,998
Mike.

115
00:06:08,735 --> 00:06:10,203
We all have our price.

116
00:06:12,472 --> 00:06:14,207
I was set up.

117
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:15,208
Sure, sure, right.

118
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:18,010
Arthur, don't go and piss me off.

119
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:22,048
Mike.

120
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:25,685
The why is not the issue.

121
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:28,454
What is,

122
00:06:29,789 --> 00:06:31,891
is they took your shield and your pension.

123
00:06:33,292 --> 00:06:35,728
Believe me, I appreciate the difficulty there must be

124
00:06:35,728 --> 00:06:38,564
in finding gainful employment with that kind of record.

125
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:43,836
Especially in security related fields.

126
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:51,611
Proceed, Mr. Bledsoe.

127
00:06:54,647 --> 00:06:57,483
(water splashing)

128
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:05,525
(bluesy ambient music)

129
00:07:50,837 --> 00:07:52,939
That house up on Barry where I live.

130
00:07:52,939 --> 00:07:55,474
I know that phone was bugged.

131
00:07:55,474 --> 00:07:58,377
You picked the phone up, it'd crack and hiss and pop.

132
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:01,514
That's why I couldn't sell my sketches.

133
00:08:02,582 --> 00:08:03,382
We got buried.

134
00:08:03,382 --> 00:08:05,218
It was Nixon, it was--

135
00:08:05,218 --> 00:08:06,319
That's too easy Art.

136
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:07,987
What's easy?

137
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:09,355
That conspiracy shit.

138
00:08:09,355 --> 00:08:11,457
I mean, it's like believing in God, ain't it?

139
00:08:12,959 --> 00:08:15,361
You know when I was a kid, about 10 or 11,

140
00:08:15,361 --> 00:08:17,196
it was right after Dr. King was shot.

141
00:08:17,196 --> 00:08:18,698
Yeah, now who do you think ordered that?

142
00:08:18,698 --> 00:08:20,499
See the FBI was all over him.

143
00:08:20,499 --> 00:08:22,001
Relax man.

144
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:24,003
You're right but that's not my point.

145
00:08:27,306 --> 00:08:29,609
Now the city sent them, I don't even know who they were man.

146
00:08:29,609 --> 00:08:31,344
These officials, white guys,

147
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:32,445
into the neighborhoods,

148
00:08:32,445 --> 00:08:34,513
to try to calm things down.

149
00:08:34,513 --> 00:08:36,148
Now most of this was just people you know,

150
00:08:36,148 --> 00:08:38,284
standing up, getting shit off their chest.

151
00:08:39,452 --> 00:08:41,420
But these guys were very polite, you know.

152
00:08:41,420 --> 00:08:43,623
They would nod, take a few notes.

153
00:08:43,623 --> 00:08:46,359
Say things like, oh that's a very valid point.

154
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:48,728
You know, same ole same ole.

155
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:50,129
But one time,

156
00:08:50,129 --> 00:08:51,998
this cat came in, brother.

157
00:08:51,998 --> 00:08:54,567
Stood up, looks these white guys right in the eye

158
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:57,403
and says, we want what you got.

159
00:08:59,338 --> 00:09:00,640
And that scared them Art.

160
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:02,308
Scared the shit of 'em.

161
00:09:02,308 --> 00:09:03,843
I mean you could feel it man.

162
00:09:03,843 --> 00:09:07,046
It wasn't tension, it was like some prime evil force.

163
00:09:07,046 --> 00:09:09,649
And you know, you knew right then,

164
00:09:09,649 --> 00:09:10,917
that there was no way in hell

165
00:09:10,917 --> 00:09:13,085
these cats were gonna give up shit.

166
00:09:13,085 --> 00:09:14,186
(alarm buzzing)

167
00:09:14,186 --> 00:09:15,021
Right.

168
00:09:20,793 --> 00:09:22,561
- [Art] Okay, so they didn't have the mahogany desk

169
00:09:22,561 --> 00:09:24,597
but those are the white haired dudes, man.

170
00:09:24,597 --> 00:09:25,798
(alarm buzzing)

171
00:09:25,798 --> 00:09:27,366
The corporate structure, political structure.

172
00:09:27,366 --> 00:09:28,568
- [Jimmy] I know that but man,

173
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,069
but that's not what I said, okay.

174
00:09:30,937 --> 00:09:31,771
Yeah?

175
00:09:31,771 --> 00:09:33,439
- [Jessica] It's me.

176
00:09:35,374 --> 00:09:36,208
What?

177
00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:37,243
For this?

178
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:38,744
She'll be an asset man.

179
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:39,779
She's quick.

180
00:09:39,779 --> 00:09:41,113
We need a female.

181
00:09:41,113 --> 00:09:43,182
That's not what she's here for man.

182
00:09:43,182 --> 00:09:44,984
Jimmy, will you just ease up?

183
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:50,189
Hi. Hey, hey.

184
00:09:50,189 --> 00:09:51,457
Mmm. Mmm.

185
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:54,760
You remember Jimmy Fuqua?

186
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,895
Sure, hi. Hey.

187
00:09:58,064 --> 00:09:59,398
- [Art] Mike, how did you get up?

188
00:09:59,398 --> 00:10:00,599
Front door was open.

189
00:10:02,568 --> 00:10:03,402
Sorry.

190
00:10:05,371 --> 00:10:07,873
Yeah, Mike Quinn, Jessica Sutter.

191
00:10:07,873 --> 00:10:08,808
- [Jessica] Hi.

192
00:10:08,808 --> 00:10:11,711
And uh, Jimmy Fuqua, Mike Quinn.

193
00:10:11,711 --> 00:10:13,346
Yeah.

194
00:10:13,346 --> 00:10:14,180
Yeah, what?

195
00:10:17,717 --> 00:10:20,953
Hey look, we all come here with clean slates, right?

196
00:10:20,953 --> 00:10:22,722
Tabula rasa, all of us.

197
00:10:24,156 --> 00:10:26,892
If anybody's got a problem with that, get out now.

198
00:10:26,892 --> 00:10:29,895
(soft upbeat music)

199
00:10:35,501 --> 00:10:37,203
Okay now look, I haven't told you everything.

200
00:10:37,203 --> 00:10:38,170
Some stuff can wait.

201
00:10:38,170 --> 00:10:39,905
And I want it to stay that way.

202
00:10:39,905 --> 00:10:42,975
What is something happens to you Aurthur?

203
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:45,778
Nothing's gonna happen to me, right Mike?

204
00:10:45,778 --> 00:10:48,748
(upbeat jazz music)

205
00:10:51,584 --> 00:10:53,519
The timing at the banks is critical.

206
00:10:54,420 --> 00:10:56,122
We gotta get 'em in and out.

207
00:10:56,122 --> 00:10:57,923
So that he can make the 10:15.

208
00:10:59,392 --> 00:11:01,227
- [Jessica] This train from Chicago, this can't be right.

209
00:11:01,227 --> 00:11:02,528
What?

210
00:11:02,528 --> 00:11:03,929
Well, it's six hours by car

211
00:11:03,929 --> 00:11:04,764
