212
00:11:04,764 --> 00:11:05,931
Right.

213
00:11:05,931 --> 00:11:07,733
Okay, well it's almost nine by train.

214
00:11:09,535 --> 00:11:11,704
That's cause it stops everywhere.

215
00:11:11,704 --> 00:11:14,040
In Hammond, Gary, where I pick up Mike,

216
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:18,144
Michigan City, Benton Harbor, everywhere.

217
00:11:18,144 --> 00:11:20,212
Mike and I will beat it back by hours.

218
00:11:20,212 --> 00:11:22,048
Okay, Arthur, you've done your homework.

219
00:11:22,048 --> 00:11:24,016
Pretty impressive stuff on paper.

220
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:26,419
Of course, you realize the whole thing blows up

221
00:11:26,419 --> 00:11:28,721
if anyone part of a, what's his face,

222
00:11:28,721 --> 00:11:30,289
the uh, chauffer. Blackwell.

223
00:11:30,289 --> 00:11:31,857
Yeah, the chauffer.

224
00:11:31,857 --> 00:11:32,792
Blackwell.

225
00:11:32,792 --> 00:11:34,660
Yeah, geez, what are ya, deaf?

226
00:11:34,660 --> 00:11:36,462
All right, what I'm saying is,

227
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:38,397
that is Blackwell is full of shit,

228
00:11:38,397 --> 00:11:40,399
it's lights out, party over.

229
00:11:42,768 --> 00:11:44,303
I'm sure he's right.

230
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:45,337
Why?

231
00:11:45,337 --> 00:11:47,006
I don't know, my gut.

232
00:11:47,006 --> 00:11:47,807
Anything else?

233
00:11:50,843 --> 00:11:51,811
Go on, tell him Art.

234
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:55,414
What?

235
00:11:56,982 --> 00:11:58,684
Well, we're both into the music.

236
00:11:58,684 --> 00:12:00,152
The music?

237
00:12:00,152 --> 00:12:02,488
Yeah, you know, jazz.

238
00:12:03,522 --> 00:12:05,491
Be-Bop & Beyond.

239
00:12:05,491 --> 00:12:08,227
It's a bonding kind of a thing, like they're in a club.

240
00:12:08,227 --> 00:12:09,061
Uh ha. Yeah.

241
00:12:10,696 --> 00:12:12,064
Look, it's not often you meet somebody

242
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:14,834
who has both Agharta and Pangaea.

243
00:12:14,834 --> 00:12:16,268
Aren't those diseases?

244
00:12:16,268 --> 00:12:18,504
No, they're two Miles Davis albums.

245
00:12:18,504 --> 00:12:19,972
(Mike laughing)

246
00:12:19,972 --> 00:12:21,173
No, it's makes sense.

247
00:12:21,173 --> 00:12:22,475
Why don't you just listen to Art?

248
00:12:23,776 --> 00:12:24,977
Look.

249
00:12:24,977 --> 00:12:27,346
How many people have a Miles album?

250
00:12:27,346 --> 00:12:28,747
Not many right.

251
00:12:28,747 --> 00:12:29,882
And those that do,

252
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:32,184
they're into the acoustic stuff.

253
00:12:32,184 --> 00:12:34,520
They hate the acid funk stuff.

254
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:36,922
Those of us that like it are few and far between.

255
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:38,824
Jimmy, you understand me on this?

256
00:12:40,025 --> 00:12:41,127
Guess it must be fate.

257
00:12:43,362 --> 00:12:44,930
Yeah, it's a club all right.

258
00:12:46,065 --> 00:12:49,268
(bluesy jazz music)

259
00:12:49,268 --> 00:12:51,604
- [Arthur] Jessie and I go to the house, first.

260
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:54,807
We set it up, then we meet you guys at the airport.

261
00:12:54,807 --> 00:12:56,609
Then we all go back to the house together.

262
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:58,244
- [Aurthur] Right.

263
00:12:58,244 --> 00:12:59,512
- [Mike] I don't don't understand why you spend $400 a night

