552
00:31:19,844 --> 00:31:20,945
Loot branches only.

553
00:31:22,513 --> 00:31:24,382
I suggest you get a pencil and paper.

554
00:31:25,783 --> 00:31:29,220
(suspenseful jazz music)

555
00:31:50,174 --> 00:31:53,544
- [Art] Are you gonna talk to me or what?

556
00:31:56,314 --> 00:31:58,116
Jessie, what could I do?

557
00:31:58,116 --> 00:32:00,285
Jimmy's right Art, it was wrong to kill him.

558
00:32:01,286 --> 00:32:02,287
I didn't pull the trigger.

559
00:32:02,287 --> 00:32:03,855
Yeah, but you brought Quinn in.

560
00:32:05,356 --> 00:32:06,658
Take a look in the mirror.

561
00:32:07,825 --> 00:32:09,827
I don't see any saints around here, do you?

562
00:32:11,462 --> 00:32:13,698
Yeah, well you didn't have to kill him.

563
00:32:13,698 --> 00:32:15,099
Don't you think I know that?

564
00:32:17,735 --> 00:32:19,370
Damn, I liked Charlie.

565
00:32:19,370 --> 00:32:22,073
Oh yeah. (laughs)

566
00:32:22,974 --> 00:32:24,342
What do you mean?

567
00:32:24,342 --> 00:32:25,476
Art, I know you.

568
00:32:26,811 --> 00:32:28,212
You think you do. No, I do.

569
00:32:31,049 --> 00:32:32,650
You think you do.

570
00:32:36,254 --> 00:32:38,923
(plane soaring)

571
00:32:43,428 --> 00:32:45,196
That's close enough. Tomorrow morning.

572
00:32:45,196 --> 00:32:46,030
It's your call. All right.

573
00:32:46,030 --> 00:32:48,700
(faint talking)

574
00:32:56,341 --> 00:32:58,710
Any news yet? No.

575
00:32:58,710 --> 00:33:00,211
You laid it out for the pilot?

576
00:33:00,211 --> 00:33:02,613
Yeah, we're back in two days.

577
00:33:02,613 --> 00:33:03,981
In the morning, in Chicago. All right.

578
00:33:03,981 --> 00:33:06,417
In the evening Toronto. Right.

579
00:33:06,417 --> 00:33:08,619
Half now, half then. Good.

580
00:33:11,823 --> 00:33:15,093
(van engine puttering)

581
00:33:49,861 --> 00:33:50,695
(Jill murmuring)

582
00:33:50,695 --> 00:33:52,897
(Jill grunting)

583
00:33:52,897 --> 00:33:54,265
- [Jessica] All right.

584
00:33:54,265 --> 00:33:55,666
What I tell you Jimmy, huh?

585
00:33:57,368 --> 00:33:59,237
Hey Art, this is cool.

586
00:34:07,512 --> 00:34:10,448
(Jill murmuring)

587
00:34:10,448 --> 00:34:13,584
- [Jessica] (whistling) Told ya, as big as a church.

588
00:34:14,986 --> 00:34:17,889
- [Jimmy] Yeah, I could have spent my summer vacations here.

589
00:34:22,026 --> 00:34:23,995
Despite some obvious limitations,

590
00:34:23,995 --> 00:34:26,431
I think you're gonna find this quite comfortable.

591
00:34:29,100 --> 00:34:31,069
Look, we're not gonna terrorize you.

592
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:33,538
Lock you in the closet for two weeks.

593
00:34:33,538 --> 00:34:36,441
We're not Satanist, we're not demented.

594
00:34:36,441 --> 00:34:38,409
This is about money.

595
00:34:40,878 --> 00:34:43,648
Look, you'll get fed three times a day.

596
00:34:44,582 --> 00:34:46,317
We'll get you magazines.

597
00:34:46,317 --> 00:34:48,953
All you have to do is stay in here,

598
00:34:48,953 --> 00:34:52,190
be quiet, be still, rest.

599
00:34:53,391 --> 00:34:55,860
You make it sound like some sort of retreat.

600
00:34:55,860 --> 00:34:57,562
That wouldn't be so bad, would it?

601
00:34:58,963 --> 00:35:01,866
This whole thing will be over in just a couple of days.

602
00:35:01,866 --> 00:35:03,201
- [Jimmy] Art, it's the news.

603
00:35:12,376 --> 00:35:15,213
(water trickling)

604
00:35:24,489 --> 00:35:27,158
(door closes)

605
00:35:27,158 --> 00:35:29,060
- [Reporter] The story this hour is the reported kidnapping

606
00:35:29,060 --> 00:35:32,263
of the daughter of one of Chicago's wealthiest families.

607
00:35:32,263 --> 00:35:34,232
Jill Luce, the 20-year-old daughter

608
00:35:34,232 --> 00:35:36,534
of financier Morgan Luc Junior,

609
00:35:36,534 --> 00:35:39,437
was abducted early this morning at O'Hare Airport.

610
00:35:39,437 --> 00:35:41,539
As Luce had just arrived from Tokyo

611
00:35:41,539 --> 00:35:43,741
where she has spent the last semester studying

612
00:35:43,741 --> 00:35:46,277
at the American University in Tokyo.

613
00:35:46,277 --> 00:35:49,347
The demands of the kidnappers are not known at this time.

614
00:35:49,347 --> 00:35:52,783
In a related story, the Luce's chauffer Charles Blackwell

615
00:35:52,783 --> 00:35:55,019
was found murdered this morning in a remote section

616
00:35:55,019 --> 00:35:56,354
of Busee Woods.

617
00:35:56,354 --> 00:35:57,955
Blackwell, aged 25,

618
00:35:57,955 --> 00:36:00,691
was scheduled to pick up Jill Luce at O'Hare.

619
00:36:18,676 --> 00:36:20,578
(door slams)

620
00:36:20,578 --> 00:36:23,314
(waves crashing)

621
00:36:26,951 --> 00:36:27,818
It's fitting huh?

622
00:36:30,154 --> 00:36:32,390
It's like the world ends right here.

623
00:36:32,390 --> 00:36:33,224
Or begins.

624
00:36:39,297 --> 00:36:41,699
Jimmy, about Blackwell- Hey.

625
00:36:41,699 --> 00:36:43,167
Nothing you can do my friend.

626
00:36:45,002 --> 00:36:45,836
Yeah.

627
00:36:48,439 --> 00:36:49,840
Where did this come from Art?

628
00:36:49,840 --> 00:36:50,841
What?

629
00:36:50,841 --> 00:36:51,676
This.

630
00:36:51,676 --> 00:36:52,944
This whole thing, man.

631
00:36:52,944 --> 00:36:54,045
Seriously? Yeah.

632
00:36:56,447 --> 00:36:58,516
It's weird man, it came to me in a dream.

633
00:37:00,685 --> 00:37:01,485
A dream?

634
00:37:02,353 --> 00:37:04,689
In a dream, I'm on a beach.

635
00:37:04,689 --> 00:37:06,791
Not like this, the Caribbean beach.

636
00:37:08,359 --> 00:37:09,794
Blue water everywhere.

637
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:14,532
And I'm digging this tunnel with my hands.

638
00:37:16,267 --> 00:37:18,035
I stop because in the distance,

639
00:37:18,035 --> 00:37:19,637
I see somebody on a horse.

640
00:37:21,472 --> 00:37:24,742
They gallop over and it turns out it's a knight.

641
00:37:24,742 --> 00:37:26,143
You know, like King Aurthur?

642
00:37:27,445 --> 00:37:29,347
Complete with a mace, the whole thing.

643
00:37:30,781 --> 00:37:32,984
He gallops over and he doesn't say anything.

644
00:37:34,986 --> 00:37:36,621
So I say, you know.

645
00:37:37,788 --> 00:37:39,557
You must be hot in that suit.

646
00:37:39,557 --> 00:37:41,492
(Jimmy laughing)

647
00:37:41,492 --> 00:37:43,227
He flips up his visor thingy.

648
00:37:44,562 --> 00:37:45,730
And it's Joe Stalin.

649
00:37:46,864 --> 00:37:48,532
The Russian? Yeah, the dictator.

650
00:37:49,967 --> 00:37:54,138
Stalin says, where are all the peasants?

651
00:37:54,138 --> 00:37:56,240
And I say, there are no peasants here.

652
00:37:57,742 --> 00:37:59,944
Too bad, says Stalin.

653
00:37:59,944 --> 00:38:00,911
I ask why.

654
00:38:02,780 --> 00:38:03,614
And he says,

655
00:38:04,782 --> 00:38:06,884
because before you slaughter them,

656
00:38:06,884 --> 00:38:08,953
they could build this damn tunnel for you.

657
00:38:08,953 --> 00:38:10,588
Think about that.

658
00:38:10,588 --> 00:38:11,722
And he gallops away.

659
00:38:12,823 --> 00:38:13,891
So I think about it.

660
00:38:16,093 --> 00:38:17,361
And I turn around and behind me now

661
00:38:17,361 --> 00:38:19,630
is this huge brick wall.

662
00:38:19,630 --> 00:38:21,699
It goes on forever, even over the water.

663
00:38:22,933 --> 00:38:24,201
And there's music coming.

664
00:38:25,569 --> 00:38:28,439
It's Miles, he's playing Some Day My Prince Will Come.

665
00:38:29,807 --> 00:38:31,642
I run up to the wall and I put my ear against it.

666
00:38:31,642 --> 00:38:35,413
I listen and there's big party going on.

667
00:38:35,413 --> 00:38:36,947
There was no way I'd get to it.

668
00:38:38,215 --> 00:38:39,884
And the graffiti says,

669
00:38:41,752 --> 00:38:42,586
take.

670
00:38:44,388 --> 00:38:46,357
You are the chosen prince.

671
00:38:46,357 --> 00:38:47,258
Take it all.

672
00:38:48,225 --> 00:38:49,727
Signed J.S.

673
00:38:52,396 --> 00:38:53,964
Then I woke up.

674
00:38:53,964 --> 00:38:55,332
We're here because of that?

675
00:38:56,734 --> 00:38:59,103
The very next day, Charlie Blackwell comes into the bar.

676
00:39:00,004 --> 00:39:00,938
We talk.

677
00:39:00,938 --> 00:39:02,173
First, it's about the music.

678
00:39:03,341 --> 00:39:05,076
Then he tells me about this gig with Luce,

679
00:39:05,076 --> 00:39:06,343
the kid being away at school.

680
00:39:06,343 --> 00:39:07,578
He lays it out man.

681
00:39:07,578 --> 00:39:09,613
Everything, he tells me everything.

682
00:39:13,451 --> 00:39:17,455
In my head, the whole time, I got this picture of Joe Stalin

683
00:39:17,455 --> 00:39:20,324
on that stupid horse, saying take.

684
00:39:21,726 --> 00:39:23,661
You're the chosen prince, take it al.

685
00:39:26,664 --> 00:39:27,698
You dream much Jimmy?

686
00:39:30,501 --> 00:39:31,736
You gotta sleep to dream.

687
00:39:33,003 --> 00:39:35,773
(waves crashing)

688
00:39:50,454 --> 00:39:52,890
(jazz music)

689
00:39:58,629 --> 00:40:01,432
Arthur, do you ever not listen to that noise?

690
00:40:01,432 --> 00:40:04,735
(laughs) You know, we gotta work on you Mike.

691
00:40:04,735 --> 00:40:07,505
Seriously. (jazz music)

692
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:10,141
Hey Mike.

693
00:40:14,278 --> 00:40:17,581
I'd do it again, if that's what you're asking.

694
00:40:18,616 --> 00:40:19,917
Yeah.

695
00:40:19,917 --> 00:40:22,319
(jazz music)

696
00:40:24,955 --> 00:40:26,490
We're playing for keeps Arthur.

697
00:40:28,292 --> 00:40:30,528
If the colored kid sees me, we're made.

698
00:40:30,528 --> 00:40:31,362
It's over.

699
00:40:35,299 --> 00:40:37,134
I was wondering, I--

700
00:40:37,134 --> 00:40:39,170
Do I feel bad that I popped the kid?

701
00:40:40,504 --> 00:40:41,939
No.

702
00:40:41,939 --> 00:40:43,474
I didn't make the world.

703
00:40:43,474 --> 00:40:45,876
(jazz music)

704
00:41:00,124 --> 00:41:02,626
(door squeaks)

705
00:41:15,105 --> 00:41:15,940
Dinner.

706
00:41:32,456 --> 00:41:34,291
There are a thousand ways

707
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:37,628
a woman can get undressed.

708
00:41:44,635 --> 00:41:45,436
Simple.

709
00:41:51,041 --> 00:41:56,013
Very simple. (Jill grunting)

710
00:42:00,618 --> 00:42:02,920
Art says to, keep the door open man.

711
00:42:10,027 --> 00:42:10,861
What?

712
00:42:11,795 --> 00:42:13,364
Nothing's going on.

713
00:42:24,542 --> 00:42:25,342
Please help me.

714
00:42:26,977 --> 00:42:30,080
I'm scared. (sobbing)

715
00:42:30,080 --> 00:42:30,915
Let me go.

716
00:42:32,650 --> 00:42:35,686
My father, they'll be a reward if you help me.

717
00:42:37,755 --> 00:42:40,224
Please. (sobbing)

718
00:42:41,959 --> 00:42:43,560
Why are you doing this?

719
00:42:44,962 --> 00:42:46,263
Is it just for the money?

720
00:42:51,368 --> 00:42:54,238
If he tries that shit again, scream.

721
00:43:02,613 --> 00:43:03,981
What if he does something to that girl?

722
00:43:03,981 --> 00:43:05,215
Have you thought about that?

723
00:43:05,215 --> 00:43:06,550
We're way behind going back Jimmy.

724
00:43:06,550 --> 00:43:08,185
You told me that nobody was gonna get hurt.

725
00:43:08,185 --> 00:43:09,987
Who do you think I am?

726
00:43:11,889 --> 00:43:13,390
I'm not God, man.

727
00:43:14,825 --> 00:43:16,060
Art, this ain't you man.

728
00:43:22,833 --> 00:43:24,835
All right Jimmy, look.

729
00:43:26,236 --> 00:43:28,572
I'm a lot closer to 50 than I am to 40, you know.

730
00:43:30,674 --> 00:43:31,942
I'm old man.

731
00:43:33,377 --> 00:43:34,211
What do I got?

732
00:43:35,846 --> 00:43:39,116
I tend a little bar, I forge a few documents.

733
00:43:39,116 --> 00:43:40,417
What kind of life is that?

734
00:43:43,887 --> 00:43:45,089
I need this Jimmy.

735
00:43:46,924 --> 00:43:47,891
I need it.

736
00:43:49,493 --> 00:43:52,763
And I'm not gonna let Quinn or anybody screw it up for me.

737
00:44:19,890 --> 00:44:22,993
(pensive jazz music)

738
00:45:01,632 --> 00:45:02,733
I'm watching you man.

739
00:45:04,101 --> 00:45:07,204
(pensive jazz music)

740
00:45:11,842 --> 00:45:12,676
Here.

741
00:45:13,711 --> 00:45:16,313
The tunnel, I figure you've got,

742
00:45:18,315 --> 00:45:20,984
45 seconds to look for the wire.

743
00:45:20,984 --> 00:45:23,720
That ain't a hell of a lot of time.

744
00:45:23,720 --> 00:45:25,389
Maybe you have a minute.

745
00:45:25,389 --> 00:45:26,590
Don't count on it.

746
00:45:26,590 --> 00:45:28,092
'Cause they're gonna be tailing him.

747
00:45:28,092 --> 00:45:29,526
Ready.

748
00:45:29,526 --> 00:45:31,829
Okay baby, you're just going for newspapers right?

749
00:45:31,829 --> 00:45:34,398
Magazines for the kid, stuff like that?

750
00:45:34,398 --> 00:45:35,232
Yeah, I know.

751
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:36,467
Nothing else?

752
00:45:36,467 --> 00:45:37,701
Yes Art, I think I can handle that.

753
00:45:49,546 --> 00:45:51,749
(papers flopping)

754
00:45:51,749 --> 00:45:52,549
Shit.

755
00:45:57,654 --> 00:45:58,689
Here.

756
00:45:58,689 --> 00:46:00,224
Let me.

757
00:46:00,224 --> 00:46:01,492
No, I'm fine, thank you.

758
00:46:01,492 --> 00:46:02,326
I got it.

759
00:46:06,697 --> 00:46:08,765
Some pretty heavy reading here.

760
00:46:08,765 --> 00:46:09,600
Yeah.

761
00:46:10,434 --> 00:46:12,102
Well thank you uh.

762
00:46:13,837 --> 00:46:14,671
Thanks.

763
00:46:17,307 --> 00:46:18,142
Well.

764
00:46:25,048 --> 00:46:25,883
Hi again.

765
00:46:27,351 --> 00:46:28,585
Hi.

766
00:46:28,585 --> 00:46:30,220
That's a lot of newspaper. Yeah.

767
00:46:31,155 --> 00:46:32,356
There's a bookstore down town

768
00:46:32,356 --> 00:46:34,324
if you're just looking for stuff to read.

769
00:46:34,324 --> 00:46:38,729
No, um, just my family and I like to keep up

770
00:46:38,729 --> 00:46:41,198
with what's going on, current events and stuff.

771
00:46:41,198 --> 00:46:42,332
Y'all have friends up here?

772
00:46:42,332 --> 00:46:44,835
Yeah, no, hmm hmm.

773
00:46:44,835 --> 00:46:45,669
Hmm hmm.

774
00:46:47,004 --> 00:46:49,973
We're staying a friend's summer place.

775
00:46:49,973 --> 00:46:50,874
Oh yeah? Hmm hmm.

776
00:46:50,874 --> 00:46:51,708
Where?

777
00:46:52,643 --> 00:46:55,212
Um, by the lake.

778
00:46:55,212 --> 00:46:56,446
That's beautiful property up there.

779
00:46:56,446 --> 00:46:57,714
Yeah.

780
00:46:57,714 --> 00:46:58,482
Not many tourists this time of year, though.

781
00:46:58,482 --> 00:46:59,850
Hmm hmm, nope.

782
00:47:02,519 --> 00:47:05,489
Sort of like a family retreat.

783
00:47:07,291 --> 00:47:09,626
- [Cashier] That's be $6.39.

784
00:47:18,101 --> 00:47:19,503
Here.

785
00:47:19,503 --> 00:47:20,737
I got it.

786
00:47:20,737 --> 00:47:22,839
Look, there's really no need for you to um.

787
00:47:22,839 --> 00:47:24,741
No problem, lead on.

788
00:47:29,279 --> 00:47:31,448
So you're from Chicago, huh?

789
00:47:31,448 --> 00:47:32,683
I didn't say I was from Chicago.

790
00:47:32,683 --> 00:47:33,917
I know.

791
00:47:33,917 --> 00:47:35,452
It's just your van has Illinois plates.

792
00:47:35,452 --> 00:47:38,622
Most people up there from Illinois are from Chicago.

793
00:47:38,622 --> 00:47:39,556
Right.

794
00:47:39,556 --> 00:47:40,791
If they were Indiana plates,

795
00:47:40,791 --> 00:47:41,692
I'd say you were from Indianapolis.

796
00:47:43,594 --> 00:47:44,528
Yeah right.

797
00:47:44,528 --> 00:47:46,463
I guess that's why I'm a cop.

798
00:47:46,463 --> 00:47:48,031
I'm putting stuff like that together all the time.

799
00:47:48,031 --> 00:47:48,999
Oh good for you.

800
00:47:50,901 --> 00:47:52,336
Well thank you.

801
00:47:52,336 --> 00:47:53,971
No, the job's undone.

802
00:47:57,708 --> 00:47:58,542
Okay.

803
00:48:04,014 --> 00:48:06,183
(door slams)

804
00:48:06,183 --> 00:48:08,518
Thank you, you've been a great help.

805
00:48:08,518 --> 00:48:09,353
My name's Ray.

806
00:48:10,621 --> 00:48:11,455
Ray Higgs.

807
00:48:11,455 --> 00:48:14,324
Uh, Jessica.

808
00:48:14,324 --> 00:48:15,892
Uh, Jessie.

809
00:48:15,892 --> 00:48:17,361
Nice to meet ya, Jessie.

810
00:48:17,361 --> 00:48:19,029
Likewise, Ray.

811
00:48:19,029 --> 00:48:20,330
Yet again, thank you.

812
00:48:21,565 --> 00:48:23,467
Uh, excuse me, Jessie.

813
00:48:23,467 --> 00:48:25,002
Yeah. But uh.

814
00:48:25,002 --> 00:48:27,671
I couldn't help but notice you're not wearing a ring.

815
00:48:27,671 --> 00:48:30,674
I was just wondering if there's a boyfriend or not,

816
00:48:30,674 --> 00:48:33,110
I'm wondering if you'd like to go out.

817
00:48:35,279 --> 00:48:36,213
You mean on a date?

818
00:48:38,215 --> 00:48:39,583
Something funny about that?

819
00:48:40,584 --> 00:48:43,086
No, no, not funny, I--

820
00:48:43,086 --> 00:48:45,155
Most people date in the big city.

821
00:48:45,155 --> 00:48:46,623
Well yeah, of course.

822
00:48:46,623 --> 00:48:50,027
But, just not with us hicks from the sticks.

823
00:48:50,027 --> 00:48:52,863
Well, Ray, look, I'm flattered really.

824
00:48:52,863 --> 00:48:55,499
